#Approach:

💡 IDEA
- Queue ko Linked List se implement karna hai.
- front -> Queue ka first node (jahan se pop hoga).
- rear -> Queue ka last node (jahan push hoga).
- Push -> tail/rear par insert.
- Pop -> head/front se remove.

⚙️ APPROACH
1. Push(x):
   - New node banao.
   - Agar queue empty hai:
     front = rear = newNode
   - Otherwise:
     rear.next = newNode
     rear = newNode

2. Pop():
   - Agar queue empty hai → return -1.
   - Agar sirf 1 node hai:
     value store karo.
     front = rear = null.
     return value.
   - Otherwise:
     front value store karo.
     front = front.next.
     return stored value.

📝 EXAMPLE

Operations:
push(2)
push(3)
pop()
push(4)
pop()

Initially:
front = null
rear = null

push(2)

front,rear
    ↓
   [2]

push(3)

front      rear
 ↓          ↓
[2] -> [3]

pop()

remove 2

front,rear
 ↓          ↓
[3]

push(4)

front       rear
 ↓           ↓
[3] -> [4]

pop()

remove 3

front,rear
 ↓           ↓
[4]

Remaining Queue = [4]

❓ WHY LINKED LIST
- Queue me insertion rear par aur deletion front se hota hai.
- Linked List me dono operations direct pointer update se ho jaate hain.
- Array ki tarah shifting ki need nahi hoti.
- Dynamic size milta hai.

⏱️ COMPLEXITY
Push  : O(1)
Pop   : O(1)
Space : O(N)

🎯 INTERVIEW POINT
- Queue efficiently banane ke liye front + rear dono pointers maintain karte hain.
- Push rear par hota hai.
- Pop front se hota hai.
- Last node remove karte waqt:
  front = rear = null karna bahut important hai.
- Empty queue condition:
  front == null
  (rear bhi null hoga).

#Code:

class MyQueue {

    class QueueNode
    {
        int data;
        QueueNode next;
        QueueNode(int a)
        {
            data = a;
            next = null;
        }
    }

    QueueNode front;
    QueueNode rear;

    void push(int a) {
        //You can code here
        //pushing means inserting at the end of the LL

        QueueNode newNode = new QueueNode(a);
        if(front == null){
          front = newNode;
          rear = newNode;
          return;
        }

        rear.next = newNode;
        rear = rear.next;
        
    }

    int pop() {
        //You can code here

        if(front == null && rear == null){
          return -1;
        }

        //Check if it is the last node
        if(front == rear){
          int temp = front.data;
          front = null;
          rear = null;
          return temp;
        }

        int x = front.data;
        front = front.next;
        return x;

    }
}
